    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Achyranthes lindenii are achyranthes tincture, achyranthes infusion, achyranthes decoction, tea, and achyranthes salve. Achyranthes tincture is a concentrated liquid extract typically made with ethanol or glycerin, used to treat various health issues including fever and rheumatism. Achyranthes infusion is a liquid extract made by steeping the plant material in hot water, often used for its antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties. Achyranthes decoction is a stronger liquid extract made by boiling the plant material in water, commonly used to treat fever, rheumatism, and respiratory issues. Achyranthes salve is a topical preparation made with the plant's resin and used to treat skin conditions and wounds due to its antimicrobial properties.",
